clamd_service 0.0.2
-------------

Scan your samples with ClamAV.

Default settings:

clamd_sock_path	/var/run/clamav/clamd.ctl
 - This is a path for the Unix socket to communicate with clamd daemon. Usually, it's at /var/run/clamav/clamd.ctl or /var/run/clamav/clamd.sock
 If you want to use clamd through the network connection, just leave this blank and fill in clamd_host_name and clamd_host_port.

clamd_host_name	127.0.0.1
 - This is used when you want to use local or remote instance of clamd

clamd_host_port	3310
 - This is used when you want to use local or remote instance of clamd

clamd_force_reload	False
 - Force clamd daemon to reload signature database

